bugs that have a demonstrable security impact on smart contracts are in' 'scope For example a Solidity program whose optimization is incorrect eg' 'leads to an incorrect output qualifies as a security bug Please note that the' 'rules of the Ethereum bounty program have precedence over this security policy' 'SSuuppppoorrtteedd VVeerrssiioonnss' 'As a general rule only the latest release gets security_policy: As part of our vulnerability disclosure policy we operate a security' 'vulnerability program through Immunefi This document serves as a complementary' 'guideline for reporting vulnerabilities and how the disclosure process is' 'managed Please refer to the official Evmos bug bounty program for uptodate' 'information' 'GGuuiiddeelliinneess' 'We require that all researchers' '     Use the Evmos bug bounty program on Immunefi to disclose all' '      vulnerabilities and avoid posting vulnerability information in public' '      places including GitHub Discord Telegram Twitter or other nonprivate' '      channels' '     Make every effort to avoid privacy violations degradation of user' '      experience disruption to production systems and destruction of data' '     Keep any information about vulnerabilities that youve discovered' '      confidential between yourself and the engineering team until the issue' '      has been resolved and disclosed' '     Avoid posting personally identifiable information privately or publicly' 'If you follow these guidelines when reporting an issue to us we commit to' '     Not pursue or support any legal action related to your research on this' '      vulnerability' '     Work with you to understand resolve and ultimately disclose the issue in' '      a timely fashion' 'DDiisscclloossuurree PPrroocceessss' 'Evmos uses the following disclosure process' '    Once a security report is received via the Immunefi Bug Bounty program' '      the team works to verify the issue and confirm its severity level' '      usingCVSS or Immunefis Vulnerability Severity Classification System' '      v' '          Two people from the affected project will review replicate and' '            acknowledge the report within  hours of the alert according to' '            the table below' '            SSeeccuurriittyy LLeevveell       HHoouurrss ttoo FFiirrsstt RReessppoonnssee AACCKK ffrroomm EEssccaallaattiioonn' '            Critical             ' '            High                 ' '            Medium               ' '            Low or Informational ' '            None                 ' '          If the report is not applicable or reproducible the Security Lead' '            or Security Secondary will revert to the reporter to request more' '            info or close the report' '          The report is confirmed by the Security Lead to the reporter' '    The team determines the vulnerabilitys potential impact on Evmos' '          Vulnerabilities with Informational and Low categorization will' '            result in creating a public issue' '          Vulnerabilities with Medium categorization will result in the' '            creation of an internal ticket and patch of the code' '          Vulnerabilities with High or Critical will result in the creation' '            of a new Security Advisory' 'Once the vulnerability severity is defined the following steps apply' '     For High and Critical' '          Patches are prepared for supported releases of Evmos in a temporary' '            private fork of the repository' '          Only relevant parties will be notified about an upcoming upgrade' '            These being validators the core developer team and users directly' '            affected by the vulnerability' '           hours following this notification relevant releases with the' '            patch will be made public' '          The nodes and validators update their Evmos and Ethermint' '            dependencies to use these releases' '          A week or less after the security vulnerability has been patched' '            on Evmos we will disclose thatthe mentioned release contained a' '            security fix' '          After an additional  weeks we will publish a public announcement' '            of the vulnerability We also publish a security Advisory on GitHub' '            and publish a CVE' '     For Informational  Low and Medium severities' '          Medium and Low severity bug reports are included in a public issue' '            and will be incorporated in the current sprint and patched in the' '            next release Informational reports are additionally categorized as' '            with low or medium priority and might not be included in the next' '            release' '          One week after the releases go out we will publish a post with' '            further details on the vulnerability as well as our response to it' 'This process can take some time Every effort will be made to handle the bug in' 'as timely a manner as possible however its important that we follow the' 'process described above to ensure that disclosures are handled consistently and' 'to keep Ethermint and its downstream dependent projects including but not' 'limited to Evmos as secure as possible' 'PPaayymmeenntt PPrroocceessss' 'The payment process will be executed according to Evmoss Immunefi Bug Bounty' 'program Rules' 'CCoonnttaacctt' 'The Evmos Security Team is constantly being monitored If you need to reach out' 'to the team directly please reach out via email securityevmosorg
